    "m_ObjectId": "3ca6db52fcd24d64950054735bedd480",
    "m_Title": "5. Mixing",
    "m_Content": "If we were to feed our color gradient straight into the Fragment base color, the metal frame would also get the same coloring. So, let's mix the two color maps: first, create a Color node and decide some metallic-looking color for the frame (gold, steel, bronze, ...). Now, we will create a Lerp node, and we will feed the new Color into the A pin, and the Sample Gradient output into the B pin. As for the interpolant, we will use the output of the Hex Lattice: this is 0 on the edge and 1 inside the hexes, so we will get B (glass color) on the hexes and A (metal color) on the edges (the frame). Plug the Lerp output into the Base Color of the Fragment shader: we're done!",
    "m_TextSize": 0,
    "m_Theme": 0,
    "m_Position": {
        "serializedVersion": "2",
        "x": 1.0,
        "y": -421.0,
        "width": 671.0,
        "height": 129.0
    },
    "m_Group": {
        "m_Id": ""
    }
}

